WebResource.PrimaryURLDescription:
This website contains resources for the course which explores various perspectives on life-meaning in philosophical and religious texts, in art, fiction, and autobiography, and in the scholarly work of philosophers and psychologists.&#x0D;
&#x0D;
The course (and website) is divided into three units:&#x0D;
&#x0D;
A Life Worth Living: Humanity’s Ideals focuses on the ancient and modern visions of harmonious existence and human flourishing;&#x0D;
&#x0D;
Threats to Meaning: Humanity’s Discontents discusses the disillusionments leading to the loss of meaning and purpose;&#x0D;
&#x0D;
Recovery of Meaning: Crises and Hopes explores the possibilities of self-discovery and growth as a result of a major crisis.&#x0D;
&#x0D;

